<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Female</emphasis>
(
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">N</emphasis>
=2): Body length 21.3-24.7 mm, wing length 19.6-22.5 mm, antenna length 3.1-3.5 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Female (Figs 36-39) resembles male. Thorax more brownish yellow. Abdomen longer, venter more brownish yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Ovipositor (Figs 36-39) elongate, reddish yellow. Cercus narrowed toward tip. Hypogynial valve shorter, narrowed toward tip.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="155" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">. India (Assam); China (Xizang).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="155" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Remarks</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">. This species was known previously only from India. This is the first record from China.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
